02:06:04.010 --> 02:06:06.430
So you could imagine doing
this outside of that session

02:06:06.430 --> 02:06:07.990
as a way to kind of bring your system

02:06:07.990 --> 02:06:09.830
back to baseline, perhaps.

02:06:09.830 --> 02:06:11.280
So if you're going to
use these sorts of things

02:06:11.280 --> 02:06:12.870
you want to think about them logically.

02:06:12.870 --> 02:06:14.830
And this also really
points to the fact that

02:06:14.830 --> 02:06:16.410
many of the things that
people are doing out there

02:06:16.410 --> 02:06:18.510
to self-medicate over use of alcohol

02:06:18.510 --> 02:06:20.870
or other substances to
try and calm themselves

02:06:20.870 --> 02:06:23.060
because they have fear, anxiety and PTSD

02:06:23.060 --> 02:06:27.080
are actually driving that
fear, anxiety and PTSD

02:06:27.080 --> 02:06:28.100
deeper into their system.

02:06:28.100 --> 02:06:30.380
Or at least is not allowing
it to relieve itself

02:06:30.380 --> 02:06:33.330
through any attempts to recount or replay

02:06:33.330 --> 02:06:35.310
and using these top-down
narrative circuits

02:06:35.310 --> 02:06:36.570
or other approaches.

02:06:36.570 --> 02:06:38.230
And the last compound I want to mention

02:06:38.230 --> 02:06:39.890
is a particularly interesting one,

02:06:39.890 --> 02:06:42.300
because it's neither an anxiolytic,

02:06:42.300 --> 02:06:45.120
nor is it something that increases

02:06:45.120 --> 02:06:47.530
overall levels of stress and alertness.

02:06:47.530 --> 02:06:52.530
But it has some kind of MDMA
ish light contour to it.

02:06:52.840 --> 02:06:56.010
It does not produce as far as we know,

02:06:56.010 --> 02:06:59.890
the same mental effects or
physical effects as MDMA

02:06:59.890 --> 02:07:02.090
by any stretch but that's...

02:07:02.090 --> 02:07:04.860
The substance I'm referring
to rather is Kava.

02:07:04.860 --> 02:07:09.860
Kava has been shown in eight
studies to have a very potent

02:07:10.070 --> 02:07:11.720
effect on reducing anxiety.

02:07:11.720 --> 02:07:15.610
But what's interesting about
kava is that kava functions

02:07:15.610 --> 02:07:17.160
by increasing GABA,

02:07:17.160 --> 02:07:19.020
this inhibitory
neurotransmitter in the brain.

02:07:19.020 --> 02:07:21.940
Remember GABA is the
inhibitory neurotransmitter

02:07:21.940 --> 02:07:24.890
that is used, that's
employed by the very neurons

02:07:24.890 --> 02:07:28.210
in the prefrontal cortex
that serve to inhibit

02:07:28.210 --> 02:07:31.020
the threat reflex.

02:07:31.020 --> 02:07:32.910
So it seems to increase GABA,

02:07:32.910 --> 02:07:35.510
but it also increases Dopamine.

02:07:35.510 --> 02:07:37.960
And that's a somewhat unusual compound.

02:07:37.960 --> 02:07:40.510
I'm not aware of many compounds
that simultaneously increase

02:07:40.510 --> 02:07:42.510
GABA and increase Dopamine.

02:07:42.510 --> 02:07:45.010
And as you recall, that
threat reflex has outputs

02:07:45.010 --> 02:07:47.190
that tap into the Dopamine system.

02:07:47.190 --> 02:07:50.650
Now that's a big leap
to go from a compound

02:07:50.650 --> 02:07:52.030
that increases GABA and Dopamine

02:07:52.030 --> 02:07:54.460
and look at a circuit spelled out on paper

02:07:54.460 --> 02:07:55.293
in front of us and say,

02:07:55.293 --> 02:07:57.170
"Oh, there's GABA and
Dopamine in this circuit

02:07:57.170 --> 02:07:59.300
and therefore this is a
good compound to take."

02:07:59.300 --> 02:08:02.380
But the effects of Kava in human studies

02:08:02.380 --> 02:08:06.270
are pretty interesting
as it relates to anxiety,

02:08:06.270 --> 02:08:08.253
stress, PTSD and fear.

02:08:09.148 --> 02:08:10.580
I'm not going to summarize
all of these because

02:08:10.580 --> 02:08:13.540
there are eight studies that I'm aware of.

02:08:13.540 --> 02:08:14.520
But I'll just mention, again,

02:08:14.520 --> 02:08:15.760
these are double blind studies.

02:08:15.760 --> 02:08:17.260
So the trial design is solid.

02:08:17.260 --> 02:08:20.160
The age ranges are anywhere from 18 to 64

02:08:20.160 --> 02:08:21.680
which is a nice broad age range.

02:08:21.680 --> 02:08:26.003
The number of subjects is
quite high both men and women.

02:08:26.970 --> 02:08:31.970
No signs of hepatotoxic signal
so meaning liver toxicity,

02:08:32.210 --> 02:08:34.350
although of course,
check with your doctor.

02:08:34.350 --> 02:08:36.880
But what was interesting
is that after a period

02:08:36.880 --> 02:08:38.890
of about three weeks of treatment

02:08:38.890 --> 02:08:42.420
with anywhere from 150 milligrams

02:08:42.420 --> 02:08:46.670
of what are called active
kava lactones, okay?

02:08:46.670 --> 02:08:49.160
So there are dosages
that relate to that kava.

02:08:49.160 --> 02:08:51.140
So a hundred milligrams of extract of Kava

02:08:51.140 --> 02:08:53.980
is a kind of a reasonable
typical dose in these studies.

02:08:53.980 --> 02:08:58.290
But that spells out to a
certain amount of Kava lactone.

02:08:58.290 --> 02:09:00.450
So you have to kind of boil down

02:09:00.450 --> 02:09:03.150
